cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.MS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the architecture of the Adapteva Epiphany many-core coprocessor and proposes a programming model for it. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on parallel programming for a many-core architecture and uses the Message Passing Interface (MPI) standard. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper reports benchmark results for four algorithms and highlights the importance of fast inter-core communication for the architecture. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the implementation of four mathematical algorithms on the Epiphany architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a programming model for a specific hardware system, the Epiphany many-core coprocessor.
